Mount Kenya University is a no go zone for these students

One of the main reason as to why the students who got locked out of university due to late registration fee is not the youthful “kashai” acquired by the university students’ industry. It was facts and circumstances that made university fees go up in Kenya, the announcement of students who got nailed on the wall on Wednesday, 11th September 2016 was filled with shock and tribulation because it was a shame that those who couldnt pay the fees had no place to be. However, the examination body number 1 where these children were locked out from was much more troubled with university students in Kenya.

The question whose answer is never found

According to news sources, there were quite a number of students who lost their lives trying to settle these little university fees since they had to accompany their parents supplying goods for registration to these universities, where are they now though.
